data.prompt:
[Verse 1]
Woke up to the dim, soft dawn
Routine whispering me along
Stillness hollowed out my mind
A gentle drift, nothing to find

[Chorus]
Floating on the quiet, letting go of noise
Tuning into softer songs, muted but poised
In this gentle pause, I finally see
The silent art of being, the peace in just to be

[Verse 2]
Overwhelmed by normal days
So I step back, let it fade
Testing out my fleeting thoughts
Calm in spaces silence brought

[Chorus]
Floating on the quiet, letting go of noise
Tuning into softer songs, muted but poised
In this gentle pause, I finally see
The silent art of being, the peace in just to be

[Outro]
Feel a little lighter, closing out the day
Carry the hush with me, in my own way
Everything doesn’t have to shout to be real
In the hush, I heal
data.title: The Silent Art of Being
